#: src/Admin/Settings.php:53
msgid "Enquire"
msgstr ""

#: src/Admin/Settings.php:98
msgid "Let shoppers ask about a product before they buy"
msgstr ""

#: src/Admin/Settings.php:99
msgid "Enquire adds an “Ask a question” button to your single product pages. Clicking it opens an accessible form (name, email, message) that emails you the question with the product details, no data is stored."
msgstr ""

#: src/Admin/Settings.php:107
msgid "General"
msgstr ""

#: src/Admin/Settings.php:108
msgid "The master switch and where enquiries are delivered."
msgstr ""

#: src/Admin/Settings.php:113
msgid "Enable enquiries"
msgstr ""

#: src/Admin/Settings.php:123
msgid "Show the “Ask a question” button on single product pages."
msgstr ""

#: src/Admin/Settings.php:129
msgid "Recipient email"
msgstr ""

#: src/Admin/Settings.php:140
msgid "Enquiries are emailed here. Leave empty to use your site’s admin email. The customer’s address is set as Reply-To so you can reply directly."
msgstr ""

#: src/Admin/Settings.php:148
msgid "Trigger button"
msgstr ""

#: src/Admin/Settings.php:149
msgid "The enquiry button shown after the add-to-cart button on the product page. Clear any text field below to restore its packaged default (shown as the greyed hint)."
msgstr ""

#: src/Admin/Settings.php:154
msgid "Button label"
msgstr ""

#: src/Admin/Settings.php:154
msgid "The wording shoppers click to open the enquiry form, e.g. “Ask a question” or “Enquire now”."
msgstr ""

#: src/Admin/Settings.php:161
msgid "Form fields"
msgstr ""

#: src/Admin/Settings.php:162
msgid "The labels inside the enquiry dialog and which fields a shopper must complete before they can send. Clear any label to restore its packaged default."
msgstr ""

#: src/Admin/Settings.php:167
msgid "Form title"
msgstr ""

#: src/Admin/Settings.php:167
msgid "The heading at the top of the dialog, set the shopper’s expectation, e.g. “Ask a question about this product”."
msgstr ""

#: src/Admin/Settings.php:168
msgid "Name field label"
msgstr ""

#: src/Admin/Settings.php:168
msgid "Sits above the name input. Customers see this wording, not “name”."
msgstr ""

#: src/Admin/Settings.php:169
msgid "Email field label"
msgstr ""

#: src/Admin/Settings.php:169
msgid "Sits above the email input. This address becomes the Reply-To, so you can answer the shopper directly."
msgstr ""

#: src/Admin/Settings.php:170
msgid "Message field label"
msgstr ""

#: src/Admin/Settings.php:170
msgid "Sits above the message box, prompt the kind of question you want, e.g. “Your question”."
msgstr ""

#: src/Admin/Settings.php:171
msgid "Submit button label"
msgstr ""

#: src/Admin/Settings.php:171
msgid "The wording on the send button inside the dialog."
msgstr ""

#: src/Admin/Settings.php:172
msgid "Require name"
msgstr ""

#: src/Admin/Settings.php:172
msgid "Shoppers cannot send until they fill in the name field."
msgstr ""

#: src/Admin/Settings.php:173
msgid "Require email"
msgstr ""

#: src/Admin/Settings.php:173
msgid "Shoppers cannot send without an email. A valid format is always enforced when an address is entered, even if this is off, but leaving it off means you may not be able to reply."
msgstr ""

#: src/Admin/Settings.php:174
msgid "Require message"
msgstr ""

#: src/Admin/Settings.php:174
msgid "Shoppers cannot send an empty enquiry."
msgstr ""

#: src/Admin/Settings.php:181
msgid "Messaging"
msgstr ""

#: src/Admin/Settings.php:182
msgid "What shoppers see after submitting, and the subject line of the email you receive. Clear any field to restore its packaged default."
msgstr ""

#: src/Admin/Settings.php:187
msgid "Success message"
msgstr ""

#: src/Admin/Settings.php:187
msgid "Shown inline the moment an enquiry sends, reassure the shopper and set a reply expectation."
msgstr ""

#: src/Admin/Settings.php:188
msgid "Error message"
msgstr ""

#: src/Admin/Settings.php:188
msgid "Shown if the email cannot be sent (e.g. a server mail error). Keep it calm and ask them to retry."
msgstr ""

#: src/Admin/Settings.php:189
msgid "Email subject"
msgstr ""

#: src/Admin/Settings.php:189
msgid "The subject line of the enquiry email you receive. {product} is replaced with the product name, so enquiries are easy to scan in your inbox."
msgstr ""

